Explanation:

*(Applying correction)* Passing an unpolarized beam through three orthogonal filters ($z, x, z$) cuts the beam intensity by half at each step: $(1/2)^3 = 1/8$. The $1/4$ key is an error assuming the beam entered already $z$-polarized.
